						<summary>

						<p>Raṅganāthasvāmi temple II Prākara, South wall.</p>						

						<p>15th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Śaka [14]15, the cyclic year Dundubhi, Kārttika śu. 15, Wednesday, lunar eclipse.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record a gift of land after purchasing it for 25 <hi rend="italic">varāha</hi> for supplying garlands, coconuts, betel leaves <hi rend="italic">etc</hi> to the god Śrīraṅgadēva by Chikka Narasāṇa-Nāyaka, son of Nāyaka. In characters of about 15th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
